HEADWORD: Colluctation
<hw>Col`luc*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>colluctatio</ets>, fr. <ets>colluctari</ets> to struggle with;
<ets>col-</ets> + <ets>luctari</ets> to struggle.]</ety> <def>A
struggling; a contention.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Colluctation</qex> with old hags and hobgoblins.</q>
<rj><qau>Dr. H. More.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
